Diagnosis. With the characteristics of the genus; podonotal-metanotal shield ( 635 long) densely setose and tuberculate: cuticular tubercles polygonal to substellate (
Fig. 34
), more or less contiguous; ca. 30 pairs of sigillar tubercles in podonotal region, metanotal region with two clusters of six sigillar tubercles; metapodal plates fused and joined to podonotal region at transverse fold; peritrematal-metapodal shield with fishscale-like reticulate ornamentation (
Fig. 32
), large gland opening about mid-shield; movable cheliceral digit (
Fig. 33
) ending in five minute teeth; soft cuticle with smoothly net-like ornamentation of narrowly elongate hexagons (
Fig. 32
), irregular polygons, and substellate cells. Tectum with smooth, rounded anterior margin. Genital shield (~ 105 long) with polygonal reticulation, surrounded by striate cuticle and seven pairs of setae (
Fig. 35
). Dorsal setae 22–30 long with ventral vane and dorsal conifer cone-like ornamentation, ventral setae similar, but strongly tapered, acuminate, barbs short. Leg setation: coxa I–IV: 3 - 3 - 2 - 1 ; trochanters I-IV: 6 - 5 - 5 - 5 ; femur I-IV: 11 (v = short spine) - 10 ( 2 basifemur) - 7-8 ( 1 on basifemur); genu I-IV: 8-11 ( 2-3 / 1, 3 / 0-2 ) - 10 ( 2 - 2 / 1, 2 / 1-2 ) - 11 ( 1-2 / 1, 3 / 1-2 ); tibia I-IV: 8-10 ( 2 - 2 / 1, 2 / 1-2 ) - 10 ( 2 - 2 / 1, 2 / 1-2 ) - 10 ( 2 - 2 / 1, 2 / 1-2 ); tarsus IV with intercalary sclerite bearing
